  <p class=3DMsoNormal><span lang=3DEN-NZ style=3D'mso-ansi-language:EN-NZ'=
>Sand
  slugs (also called Bakdurs) are large silicon-based organisms that someti=
mes
  inhabit Desert planets.<o:p></o:p></span></p>
  <p class=3DMsoNormal><span lang=3DEN-NZ style=3D'mso-ansi-language:EN-NZ'=
>Sand slugs
  burrow beneath the vast desert sands, occasionally surfacing to seek out
  prey. They eat metallic minerals they find in rocks, but also eagerly dev=
our
  any space ships or bases that cross their path.<o:p></o:p></span></p>
  <p class=3DMsoNormal><span lang=3DEN-NZ style=3D'mso-ansi-language:EN-NZ'=
>Like
  their cousin the space slug, sand slugs move quite slowly. However they p=
ose
  a serious threat to stationary platforms like mining stations located at
  Desert planets.<o:p></o:p></span></p>
